{"word":"H1730 - דֹּוד - dôwd - dode - Beloved","slug":"H1730","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דֹּוד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dôwd"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>dode"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beloved"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D3;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D5;&#x05D3; - do&#x0302;d  do&#x0302;d</b> - <i>dode, dode</i><p/>From an unused root meaning properly to <i>boil</i>, that is, (figuratively) to <i>love</i>; by implication a <i>love token</i>, <i>lover</i>, <i>friend</i>; specifically an <i>uncle: - </i>(well-) beloved, father&rsquo;s brother, love, uncle."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1731\">H1731</a>, <a href=\"#/H1732\">H1732</a>, <a href=\"#/H1733\">H1733</a>, <a href=\"#/H1734\">H1734</a>, <a href=\"#/H1735\">H1735</a>, <a href=\"#/H1736\">H1736</a>, <a href=\"#/H1737\">H1737</a>"}]}